</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDBE937FFB2C838FF72FCEBFB2C278C" blockId="8.[136,1452,158,1157]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FF72FCEBFE172081" bold="true" box="[189,428,878,904]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">Taxonomic remarks</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB2C838FE00FCEAFD592081" box="[463,738,879,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="majoricanum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FE00FCEAFD592081" box="[463,738,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">Hieracium majoricanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been included into the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB2C838FB69FCEAFAFC2081" box="[1190,1351,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elisaeanum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FB69FCEAFAFC2081" box="[1190,1351,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">H. elisaeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFB2C838FA9BFCEBFEC620A5" author="Greuter, W. &amp; Raab-Straube, E. von" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" refId="ref7701" refString="Greuter, W. &amp; Raab-Straube, E. von (Eds.) (2008) Med - Checklist. A critical inventory of vascular plants of the circum - Mediterranean countries, 2. Dicotyledones (Compositae). Organization for the Phyto - Taxonomic Investigation of the Mediterranean Area (OPTIMA), Geneve, cclxxxvii + 798 pp." type="book" year="2008">Greuter &amp; Raab-Straube 2008</bibRefCitation>
, Mateo 
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FE1AFC16FDBE20A5" box="[469,517,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">et al</emphasis>
. 2017) or 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB2C838FDB8FC16FB9320A5" authority="(Mateo &amp; Egido 2017)" baseAuthorityName="Mateo &amp; Egido" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[631,1064,914,940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="loscosianum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FDB8FC16FC9F20A5" box="[631,804,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">H. loscosianum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFB2C838FCFDFC17FB9B20A5" author="Mateo, G. &amp; Egido, F." box="[818,1056,914,940]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" refId="ref8422" refString="Mateo, G. &amp; Egido, F. del (2017) Estudio monografico de los generos Hieracium y Pilosella en Espana. Con referencias a Portugal y los Pirineos franceses. Monografias de Botanica Iberica, nº 20, Jolube, Jaca, 422 pp." type="book" year="2017">Mateo &amp; Egido 2017</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
most likely by a misunderstanding of the protologue and lack of studies of the original material. In our opinion, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB2C838FC15FC32FB2B20D9" box="[986,1168,951,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="majoricanum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FC15FC32FB2B20D9" box="[986,1168,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">H. majoricanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should not be ascribed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB2C838FF47FC5EFE9020FD" box="[136,299,986,1012]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eliaseanum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FF47FC5EFE9020FD" box="[136,299,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">H. eliaseanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to several diagnostic morphological features. In fact, the Balearic plant should be included within the so-called 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB2C838FED4FC7AFE042711" box="[283,447,1023,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aragonense">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FED4FC7AFE042711" box="[283,447,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">H. aragonense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFB2C838FDDCFC7BFCB92711" author="Mateo, G. &amp; Egido, F." box="[531,770,1022,1048]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" refId="ref8422" refString="Mateo, G. &amp; Egido, F. del (2017) Estudio monografico de los generos Hieracium y Pilosella en Espana. Con referencias a Portugal y los Pirineos franceses. Monografias de Botanica Iberica, nº 20, Jolube, Jaca, 422 pp." type="book" year="2017">Mateo &amp; Egido 2017</bibRefCitation>
), most likely a non-natural lineage only comprising polyploid plants. Preliminary results suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB2C838FD9FFBA6FCB02735" box="[592,779,1059,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="majoricanum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FD9FFBA6FCB02735" box="[592,779,1059,1084]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">H. majoricanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly differs from the closely related 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB2C838FB12FBA6FA3E2735" box="[1245,1413,1059,1084]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aragonense">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FB12FBA6FA3E2735" box="[1245,1413,1059,1084]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">H. aragonense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by indumentum features; its stems and pedicels are densely covered by numerous stellate hairs (vs. glabrous, or rarely sparsely hairy) and the phyllaries are densely covered by glandular hairs (vs. sparsely hairy).
</paragraph>
